'''Darrin P. Gayles''' is an [[Florida]] [[Florida Circuit Courts|Circuit Court Judge]] and is a nominee to be a [[United States federal judge|United States District Judge]] of the [[United States District Court for the Southern District of Florida]].

==Biography==

Gayles received a [[Bachelor of Arts]] degree in 1990 from [[Howard University]]. He received a [[Juris Doctor|Juris Doctorate]] in 1993 from the [[George Washington University Law School]]. He began his career as an Assistant State Attorney in the Miami-Date State Attorney's Office from 1993 to 1997. From 1997 to 1999, he served as an Assistant District Counsel at the [[United States Immigration and Naturalization Service]]. From 1999 to 2004, he served as an Assistant United States Attorney for the Southern District of Florida. From 2004 to 2011, he served as a County Judge in [[Miami-Dade County, Florida|Miami-Dade County]] within the Eleventh Judicial Circuit. Since 2001, he has served as a [[Florida Circuit Courts|Circuit Court Judge]] in the [[Eleventh Judicial Circuit Court of Florida|Eleventh Judicial Circuit]].<ref>[http://www.whitehouse.gov/the-press-office/2014/02/05/president-obama-announces-intent-nominate-four-serve-united-states-distr "President Obama Announces Intent to Nominate Four to Serve on the United States District Courts" White House, February 5, 2014]</ref>

==Nomination to district court==

On February 5, 2014, [[Barack Obama|President Obama]] announced his intent to nominate Gayles to serve as a United States District Judge of the United States District Court for the Southern District of Florida. <!--to the seat being vacated by Judge [[John Phil Gilbert]], who is taking [[senior status]] on March 15, 2014. Her nomination is currently pending before the [[United States Senate Committee on the Judiciary|Senate Judiciary Committee]].<ref>[http://www.whitehouse.gov/the-press-office/2014/01/16/presidential-nominations-sent-senate "Presidential Nominations Sent to the Senate" White House, January 16, 2014]</ref>-->

